- 1.2.0 | Mar 08 2026:
[New] assert_json_field — extract and assert JSON field values with dot-notation
      for nested fields; uses python3 -c for parsing
[New] assert_json_array_length — assert JSON array length at a given key path
[New] assert_csv_row_count — assert CSV data row count excluding header
[New] assert_csv_header — assert CSV header contains expected column names
[New] assert_output_line_count — assert output line count (exact or min/max range)
[New] assert_file_perms — assert file permissions via stat -c '%a'
[New] assert_process_running / assert_process_not_running — process existence
      assertions via pgrep -f
[New] uat_wait_for_condition — poll a command until success or timeout with
      configurable UAT_POLL_INTERVAL (default 0.5s); hard timeout protection
[New] uat_wait_for_file — wait for file to exist and be non-empty
[New] uat_wait_for_log — wait for pattern to appear in log file
[New] uat_cleanup_processes — graceful pkill + SIGKILL fallback with wait;
      tolerates already-dead processes
[New] 32 new self-tests for all 12 new UAT helper functions; 194 tests total
